Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Import errors between modules

Solution: Ensure all scripts are in the same directory or add proper path handling
Issue: JSON file not found errors

Solution: Check file paths and ensure directories exist before saving
Issue: Data not persisting between phases

Solution: Verify data is being saved to files and loaded correctly in subsequent phases
Conclusion
This lab introduced the ADDIE model for systematic training development. You created a Python-based framework to manage all five phases: Analyze, Design, Develop, Implement, and Evaluate. This structured approach ensures training programs are well-planned, effectively delivered, and continuously improved based on evaluation data.

The ADDIE model is widely used in corporate training, educational institutions, and government organizations. By completing this lab, you've gained practical experience in instructional design methodology that can be applied to various training and development projects.

Key Takeaways:

ADDIE provides a systematic approach to training development
Each phase builds upon the previous phase's outputs
Documentation and data tracking are essential throughout
Evaluation drives continuous improvement
The model is flexible and can be adapted to different contexts
